      • putTypedTemporary

        <B extends V> Pair<? extends V,TypeInfo<? extends V>> putTypedTemporary(K key,
                                                                        B value,
                                                                        TypeInfo<B> type)
        Temporary associates key and a value reified type (type) to a value. Obs: Keys are unique, if the same key is associated to a different reified value type, old key should be replaced.
        Type Parameters:
        B - Type of value.
        Parameters:
        key - Key to associate
        value - Value to associate to key.
        type - Reified type of value.
        Returns:
        Replaced value and reified type associated to key, or Pair.nullPair() if no one value was replaced.

      • putTyped

        default <B extends V> Pair<? extends V,TypeInfo<? extends V>> putTyped(K key,
                                                                       B value,
                                                                       TypeInfo<B> type,
                                                                       boolean isTemporary)
        Associates key and a value reified type (type) to a value. Obs: Keys are unique, if the same key is associated to a different reified value type, old key should be replaced. Default implementation calls putTypedTemporary(Object, Object, TypeInfo) is isTemporary is true or call TypedMap.putTyped(Object, Object, TypeInfo) if not.
        Type Parameters:
        B - Type of value.
        Parameters:
        key - Key to associate
        value - Value to associate to key.
        type - Reified type of value.
        isTemporary - True to associates temporary, temporary values is removed when the value is retrieved.
        Returns:
        Replaced value and reified type associated to key, or Pair.nullPair() if no one value was replaced.
